        private static void TimedExitTest (
            ref int pintTestNbr ,
            CmdLneArgsBasic cmdArgs )
        {
            const string PARAMETERS_MSG_TPL = @"{2}Test # {0}: This test displays a countdown of {1} seconds.{2}";
            const string COUNTDOWN_MSG_TPL = @"Test ending in {0} seconds";
            const string COUNTDOWN_OVER = @"Test ended.{0}";
            const string SAMPLE_EXCEPTION_REPORT = @"This is a test exception. This is only a test.";
            const string PROPERTY_NOT_SET = @"NONE: The ErrorMessageColors property is null (uninitialized).";

            const int ONE_SECOND = 1000;
            const uint TIME_IS_UP = 0;

            uint uintWaitSeconds = GetUintSwitchByName (
                cmdArgs ,
                SW_WAITTIME ,
                SW_WAITTIME_DEFAULT );

            if ( pintTestNbr == StandardConstants.ZERO )
                pintTestNbr++;

            Console.WriteLine (
                PARAMETERS_MSG_TPL ,    // Format string
                pintTestNbr ,           // Token 0
                uintWaitSeconds ,       // Token 1
                Environment.NewLine );  // Token 2

            FixedConsoleWriter fcwCountdownClock = new FixedConsoleWriter (
                ConsoleColor.Blue ,     // Text color
                ConsoleColor.Yellow );  // Background color

            for ( uint uintSecodsLeft = uintWaitSeconds ;
                       uintSecodsLeft > TIME_IS_UP ;
                       uintSecodsLeft-- )
            {
                fcwCountdownClock.Write (
                    COUNTDOWN_MSG_TPL ,
                    uintSecodsLeft );

                System.Threading.Thread.Sleep ( ONE_SECOND );
            }   // for ( uint uintSecodsLeft = uintWaitSeconds ; uintSecodsLeft > TIME_IS_UP ; uintSecodsLeft-- )

            fcwCountdownClock.ScrollUp ( );
            Console.WriteLine (
                COUNTDOWN_OVER ,
                Environment.NewLine );

            try
            {
                MessageInColor micParams = new MessageInColor ( ConsoleColor.Blue , ConsoleColor.White );
                micParams.ColorWriteLine ( "AppExceptionLogger properties:{0}" , Environment.NewLine );
                ExceptionLogger exlMine = ApplicationInstance.GetTheSingleInstance ( ).AppExceptionLogger;

                micParams.ColorWriteLine ( "    AppEventSourceID         = {0}" , exlMine.AppEventSourceID );
                micParams.ColorWriteLine ( "    AppStackTraceDisposition = {0}" , exlMine.AppStackTraceDisposition );
                micParams.ColorWriteLine ( "    AppSubsystem             = {0}" , exlMine.AppSubsystem );

                if ( exlMine.ErrorMessageColors == null )
                {
                    micParams.ColorWriteLine ( "    MessageBackgroundColor   = {0}" , PROPERTY_NOT_SET );
                    micParams.ColorWriteLine ( "    MessageForegroundColor   = {0}" , PROPERTY_NOT_SET );
                }
                else
                {
                    micParams.ColorWriteLine ( "    MessageBackgroundColor   = {0}" , exlMine.ErrorMessageColors.MessageBackgroundColor );
                    micParams.ColorWriteLine ( "    MessageForegroundColor   = {0}" , exlMine.ErrorMessageColors.MessageForegroundColor );
                }   // if ( exlMine.ErrorMessageColors == null )

                micParams.ColorWriteLine ( "    EventLoggingState        = {0}" , exlMine.EventLoggingState );
                throw new Exception ( SAMPLE_EXCEPTION_REPORT );
            }
            catch ( Exception exThis )
            {
                ApplicationInstance saiMe = ApplicationInstance.GetTheSingleInstance ( );
                string strMsg = saiMe.AppExceptionLogger.ReportException (
                    exThis ,
                    System.Reflection.MethodBase.GetCurrentMethod ( ).Name );

                #if SHOW_EXCPT_MSG
                    MessageInColor.WriteLine (
                        ConsoleColor.White ,
                        ConsoleColor.DarkRed ,
                        strMsg );
                #endif  // #if SHOW_EXCPT_MSG
            }   // Try/Catch block (no Finally block needed)
        }   // private static void TimedExitTest

            Exception pexAnyKind ,
            string pstrRoutineLabel ,
            string pstrMessageTemplate )

            string strRawMsg = pexAnyKind.Message;

            string strExceptionTypeName = pexAnyKind.GetType ( ).FullName;

        public static void TimedWait (
            uint puintWaitSeconds ,
            string pstrCountdownWaitingFor ,
            ConsoleColor pclrTextColor ,
            ConsoleColor pclrTextBackgroundColor ,
            InterruptCriterion penmInterruptCriterion )
        {
        puintWaitSeconds        5                                                                                   uint
        pstrCountdownWaitingFor "A TimeedWaitTest"                                                                  string
        pclrTextColor           Green                                                                               System.ConsoleColor
        pclrTextBackgroundColor Black                                                                               System.ConsoleColor
        penmInterruptCriterion  None                                                                                WizardWrx.ConsoleAppAids.DisplayAids.InterruptCriterion

        uintSecondsToWait       0                                                                                   uint
        strCountdownWaitingFor  null                                                                                string
        cwDisplayColors         null                                                                                WizardWrx.ConsoleAppAids.FixedConsoleWriter

        COUNTDOWN_MSG_TPL       "{0} in {1} seconds"                                                                string
        COUNTDOWN_WAITING_FOR   "Program ending"                                                                    string
        ONE_SECOND              1000                                                                                int
        TIME_IS_UP              0                                                                                   uint
        WAIT_TIME_DEFAULT       30                                                                                  uint


            if ( puintWaitSeconds == TIME_IS_UP )
                uintSecondsToWait = WAIT_TIME_DEFAULT;
            else
                uintSecondsToWait = puintWaitSeconds;

        uintSecondsToWait       5                                                                                   uint

            if ( string.IsNullOrEmpty ( pstrCountdownWaitingFor ) )
                strCountdownWaitingFor = COUNTDOWN_WAITING_FOR;
            else
                strCountdownWaitingFor = pstrCountdownWaitingFor;

        strCountdownWaitingFor  "A TimeedWaitTest"                                                                  string

            FixedConsoleWriter cwDisplayColors = new FixedConsoleWriter (
                pclrTextColor ,
                pclrTextBackgroundColor );

        cwDisplayColors {WizardWrx.ConsoleAppAids.FixedConsoleWriter}                                               WizardWrx.ConsoleAppAids.FixedConsoleWriter
            _cw                 {WizardWrx.ConsoleAppAids.MessageInColor}                                           WizardWrx.ConsoleAppAids.MessageInColor
            _intInitialCol      0                                                                                   int
            _intInitialRow      9                                                                                   int
            _strFiller          "                                                                              "    string
            Static members
            LEFT_EDGE           0                                                                                   int
            NONE                0                                                                                   int
            WHOLE               -1                                                                                  int


            for ( uint uintSecodsLeft = puintWaitSeconds ;
                       uintSecodsLeft > TIME_IS_UP ;
                       uintSecodsLeft-- )
            {
                cwDisplayColors.Write (
                    COUNTDOWN_MSG_TPL ,
                    strCountdownWaitingFor ,
                    uintSecodsLeft );

                System.Threading.Thread.Sleep ( ONE_SECOND );
            }   // for ( uint uintSecodsLeft = puintWaitSeconds ; uintSecodsLeft > TIME_IS_UP ; uintSecodsLeft-- )
